# Mobile Responsive

Every screen must be usable at **375px** (phone), **768px** (tablet), and desktop.

## Layout

- **Mobile-first Tailwind**: base styles for small screens; enhance with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- No fixed side-by-side layouts without a mobile fallback (`flex-col`, Sheet drawer, or hidden panel)
- Side panels (preview, steps nav): **closed/hidden by default below `md`**; open via toggle/Sheet
- Navigation below `lg`: **Sheet drawer** + menu button — not a persistent `w-64` sidebar
- Use `min-w-0` and `truncate` in flex rows to prevent horizontal overflow

## Spacing and touch

- Page padding: `p-4 sm:p-6 md:p-8`
- Card padding: `p-4 sm:p-6`
- Primary controls: touch target ≥ 44px (`min-h-11`, `size-11`, or `py-3`)
- Button groups on mobile: `flex-col-reverse sm:flex-row` with `w-full sm:w-auto` where helpful

## Patterns

| Pattern | Mobile | Desktop |
|---------|--------|---------|
| App sidebar | Sheet drawer (`< lg`) | Fixed sidebar (`lg+`) |
| Step nav | Sheet / toggle (`< md`) | Fixed aside (`md+`) |
| Editor preview | Sheet, closed default (`< md`) | Side panel (`md+`) |
| Grids | 1 column base | `sm:` / `md:` columns |
| Page headers | Stack title + CTA | `sm:flex-row` |

## Copy and testing

- All user-facing text via `src/lib/labels.ts` — English only
- Before claiming done: verify layout at 375px, 768px, and 1280px
- Avoid horizontal scroll; `overflow-x: hidden` on `body` is a safety net only

